üî¨This is a nightly-only experimental API. (`maybe_uninit_write_slice`¬†[#79995](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/79995))

Clones the elements from `src` to `this`, returning a mutable reference to the now initialized contents of `this`. Any already initialized elements will not be dropped.

If `T` implements `Copy`, use [`copy_from_slice`](about:blank/union.MaybeUninit.html#method.copy_from_slice "associated function std::mem::MaybeUninit::copy_from_slice")

This is similar to [`slice::clone_from_slice`](about:blank/primitive.slice.html#method.clone_from_slice "method slice::clone_from_slice") but does not drop existing elements.

##### [¬ß](#panics-1)Panics

This function will panic if the two slices have different lengths, or if the implementation of `Clone` panics.

If there is a panic, the already cloned elements will be dropped.

##### [¬ß](#examples-13)Examples

```
#![feature(maybe_uninit_write_slice)]
